english:
  title: Inscription on the Hermitage of Master Hyeonwu the Great Zen Practitioner
  author: Kim Ryun
  language: eng
  text: |-
    My nature has always loved the mountains dearly—
    Yet loving mountains, what urgency calls me back?
    The mountain spirit must laugh at this dusty-world wanderer,
    Whose days are endless bustle, never knowing a moment's rest.
  footnotes:
    - The 'mountain spirit' (山靈) represents the personified essence of the mountain, which observes the poet's conflicted attachment to both mountain retreat and worldly affairs.
    - The 'red dust' (紅塵) is a Buddhist metaphor for the mundane world of human desires and attachments, in contrast to the spiritual purity of mountain solitude.
